Video 18
creating node modules that is production ready and cross platform:

STEPS:

1. as node modules things are exported into the .js file and so while creating them we start with (in index.js file the creation of node module)
   `module.export = () => {.........};`


ALL FILES
main files - [index.js , package.js ,npmrc]
extra files -

1)code-of-conduct
    >>npx conduct
2)license 
    >>npx licensed MIT
3).editorconfig
4).gitattributes
5).gitignore
6).npmrc //when making node modules we do not want to create package-lock file and so this is needed
7).prettierrc
